title: IntelliSense doesn't show imported type in completion list
body:
When I import a type from another file, IntelliSense doesn't suggest it in the completion list.

Steps to reproduce:
1. Create file types.ts with export interface MyType { prop: string }
2. In another file, type const x: My and trigger completions
3. MyType should appear but doesn't

Expected: MyType should be in the completion list
Actual: MyType is not shown

This works fine in other editors, seems to be VS Code specific.

TypeScript Version: 5.3.0
VS Code Version: 1.85.0
